<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-31T00:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-31T00:35:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14567:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-31T09:00:00+03:25">August 31, 1941—9
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 1—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>123. At my first meeting with the Foreign Minister yesterday he
                                informed me that the Shah was most disappointed that his request
                                through this Legation and his Legation at Washington for American
                                good offices had received no reply.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>